				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">A lot of old PC games used a separate update region from the screen region. When a spawn location entered the update region the enemy would spawn, and when the enemy was no longer in the update region it would deactivate. Some games used an update region that was two or three times as big as the screen, giving a more persistent feeling to the action.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

